<taxonomicName box="[322,577,1861,1885]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Paederomimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="191" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrinus">
<emphasis box="[322,577,1861,1885]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="191">Paederomimus nigrinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be identified among other Neotropical 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirby" authorityYear="1837" box="[1050,1173,1861,1885]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="191" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Philonthina">Philonthina</taxonomicName>
with similar habitus and color pattern by the following combination of characters: antennae with third segment longer than 1.5 times as long as second segment, two apical segments testaceous, distinctly paler than preceding segments; head with postgenal ridge developed ventrally but not joining ventral basal ridge medially and labial palpi with third segment distinctly shorter than second segment.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
